The paper deals with optimization in partial monitoring games, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several subfields in computer science. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper proposes an algorithm for minimizing regret in partial monitoring games, which is a common problem in reinforcement learning. The paper also uses game theory concepts, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Additionally, the paper proposes an algorithm that uses optimization techniques, which could place it under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also uses mathematical analysis to derive bounds on the regret, which could suggest that it belongs to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.IT (Information Theory).
